{"TopicId":192047,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Is anyone having this torque bug?","CreatedByName":"Neon7","CreatedById":203085,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-01T08:29:45Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Neon7","CreatedById":203085,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-01T08:29:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo for some reason, my game has a bug where when it (the bug)\u00A0shows up, I can\u0027t turn \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E off, or else my spacecraft will start to torque in one specific direction, and no, I cannot counteract this torque because the opposite direction won\u0027t turn, like I literally can\u0027t turn it the other way! And if I\u00A0do turn \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E back on, it works fine, except I can\u0027t turn it in one direction.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExp(with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E): I can turn it (the spacecraft) left/right, up, but not down (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E or\u00A0reaction wheels, no matter what)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExp(without \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E): Just starts turning\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThx\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOS - Windows10-Pavilion computer\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nno mods\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVersion 1.9.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-18T10:11:37Z\u0022 title=\u002203/18/2020 10:11  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 18, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Neon7\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-01T08:47:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReminds me of another thread I\u0027ve seen some time ago:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002283752\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4190159849\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/190638-sas-issues-craft-spinning-wildlypitch-controls-always-move-towards-prograde/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo cause or actual solution was found, the player reverted to an older save game and the issue was gone.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you try out an older save game, does the bug occur then too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-03T06:34:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat might be as simple as a design issue with your craft. Care to share?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Neon7","CreatedById":203085,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-18T10:09:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223750047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583052454\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/1/2020 at 1:47 AM, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReminds me of another thread I\u0027ve seen some time ago:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002283752\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2196295794\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/190638-sas-issues-craft-spinning-wildlypitch-controls-always-move-towards-prograde/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:210px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo cause or actual solution was found, the player reverted to an older save game and the issue was gone.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you try out an older save game, does the bug occur then too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes it does seem to still occur. Yes this is the same problem as your... quote?\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223751180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583217280\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161238\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Anth12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/2/2020 at 11:34 PM, Anth12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat might be as simple as a design issue with your craft. Care to share?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, this happens in space and it has nothing to do with the design, it just starts turning.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"4x4cheesecake","CreatedById":187982,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-19T09:21:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you set the trim control by accident in one direction? \u0022Alt \u002B X\u0022 should reset the trim settings\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-21T12:37:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\npretty sure that trim doesnt work in space?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"4x4cheesecake","CreatedById":187982,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-21T16:17:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223759302\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584794229\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161238\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Anth12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Anth12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\npretty sure that trim doesnt work in space?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does, it will affect the reaction wheels in your craft and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, especially when you set it to a specific direction, will \u0022override\u0022 the trim. But if you turn \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E off, the trim will turn the ship around without any inputs so pretty much the problem described in \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Neon7","CreatedById":203085,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-14T23:38:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223759350\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584807435\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187982\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00224x4cheesecake\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/21/2020 at 9:17 AM, 4x4cheesecake said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does, it will affect the reaction wheels in your craft and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, especially when you set it to a specific direction, will \u0022override\u0022 the trim. But if you turn \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E off, the trim will turn the ship around without any inputs so pretty much the problem described in \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIll try this and if it works, ill respond asap! thx\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: thank you so much for fixing this problem i\u0027ve had for a few months, and thank you for taking the time out of your day to answer my question!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-14T23:59:04Z\u0022 title=\u002204/14/2020 11:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 14, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Neon7\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EA response\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}